%2C%20an%20internal%20memo%20shows%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227166%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Delta%20plane.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f9038438bee05c96983a38%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224777%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDelta%20is%20experiencing%20an%20abnormally%20high%20volume%20of%20flight%20cancellations%20compared%20to%20its%20mainline%20counterparts.%3Cp%3ESAUL%20LOEB%20%2F%20AFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDelta%20canceled%20hundreds%20of%20flights%20this%20weekend%2C%20while%20American%20and%20United%20canceled%20a%20handful.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20internal%20memo%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%20shows%20the%20reason%20is%20crew%20scheduling.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDelta%20is%20using%20a%20complex%20scheduling%20system%20to%20fill%20last-minute%20trips%2C%20which%20can%20be%20inefficient.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-what-delta-new-business-class-suite-will-look-like-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDelta%20Air%20Lines%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20canceling%20hundreds%20of%20flights%20%E2%80%94%20far%20more%20than%20its%20competitors%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20strained%20scheduling%20system%20is%20largely%20to%20blame%2C%20Business%20Insider%20has%20learned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Friday%2C%20Delta%20has%20canceled%20about%20500%20flights%2C%20while%20American%20Airlines%20and%20United%20Airlines%20have%20canceled%20a%20combined%20total%20of%2080%20flights.%20Delta%20canceled%20some%20flights%20in%20recent%20days%20within%20hours%20of%20boarding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20apologize%20to%20our%20customers%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-when-your-flight-is-canceled-2016-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehigher%20than%20usual%20cancellations%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20weekend%20due%20to%20crew%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20internal%20memo%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%20sheds%20more%20light%20on%20the%20crew%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20April%2024%20memo%20by%20Ryan%20Gumm%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20Flight%20Operations%2C%20cited%20a%20sharp%20decline%20in%20pilots%20taking%20on%20extra%20flights%20beyond%20their%20regular%20schedules.%20Acceptance%20rates%20for%20these%20open%20trips%20have%20plunged%20to%202%25%20from%20about%2037%25%20year%20over%20year.%20That%20collapse%20has%20slowed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDelta's%20%3C%2Fa%3Eability%20to%20fill%20last-minute%20staffing%20gaps%2C%20the%20memo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20fill%20the%20gaps%2C%20Delta%20is%20using%20a%20complex%20staffing%20system%2C%20known%20internally%20as%2023.M.7%2C%20to%20cover%20trips%20quickly.%20This%20system%20can%20be%20inefficient%2C%20incentivizing%20pilots%20to%20pick%20up%20unstaffed%20trips%20while%20leaving%20holes%20elsewhere.%20It%20also%20means%20that%20Delta%20is%20typically%20paying%20pilots%20a%20premium%20for%20these%20last-minute%20trip%20fills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B23.M.7%2C%20never%20intended%20for%20consistent%20daily%20operations%2C%20is%20now%20being%20used%2010%20to%2015%20times%20more%20than%20last%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20memo%20said.%20The%20company%20is%20currently%20renegotiating%20the%20union%20contract%2C%20which%20requires%20the%20use%20of%20the%20pilot%20scheduling%20system%20in%20certain%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20does%20that%20leave%20Delta%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlight%20operations-related%20cancellations%20are%20now%20more%20than%2010%20times%20higher%20than%20historical%20levels%20and%20account%20for%2035%25%20of%20Delta's%20mainline%20cancellations%2C%20up%20from%20just%207%25%20last%20year%2C%20the%20memo%20said.%20Flight%20operations%20refer%20to%20the%20company's%20staffing%20function%2C%20versus%20cancellations%20due%20to%20weather%20or%20other%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDelta%20is%20required%20to%20work%20with%20travelers%20whose%20flights%20have%20been%20canceled%20to%20find%20the%20next%20available%20option%20at%20no%20extra%20cost%3B%20those%20affected%20may%20be%20able%20to%20claim%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflights-delayed-canceled-travel-plans-what-to-do%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompensation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20travel%20credit%2C%20hotel%20rooms%2C%20or%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Delta%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20recent%20cancellations%20are%20%26quot%3Bnot%20consistent%20with%20the%20operational%20reliability%20that%20Delta%20is%20known%20for%20and%20has%20our%20full%20attention.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20alleviate%20pressure%2C%20Delta%20has%20been%20increasing%20pilot%20reserve%20levels%20and%20accelerating%20pilot%20hiring%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20The%20company%20has%2020%25%20more%20pilots%20than%20in%202019%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20operation%20today%20is%20far%20more%20complex%20than%20it%20was%2015%20years%20ago%2C%20yet%20many%20elements%20of%20trip%20coverage%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-says-scheduling-system-played-a-role-in-flight-meldown-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Escheduling%20practices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20pilot%20access%20haven't%20evolved%20at%20the%20same%20pace%2C%26quot%3B%20Gumm%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20rely%20on%20old%20structures%20and%20expect%20improved%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-canceling-flights-crew-scheduling-challenges-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777928960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f90390b3045b292f636985%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22ori